The detained diplomats were released 444 days after the Algerian government's negotiating intervention.
In the US, his fate caused a wave of solidarity and animosity against Iran.
Failure in Iran contributed decisively to Jimmy Carter's defeat against Ronald Reagan in the 1980 presidential election.
The film "Argo" by director and actor Ben Affleck themes an episode of this story, which harvested a small success for America.
Shortly before occupying the embassy, six employees escaped from the building.
After a complicated journey, they ended up at the residence of the Canadian embassy.
The CIA, in collaboration with Canadian authorities, managed to get them out of Iran, for which a cover-up story helped an extravagant point: they came out with Canadian passports, as members of the film team that examined the location in the country for the shooting of a superproduction of science fiction.
Combination of genders
