Ben Affleck has re-started his career.
The actor, who had been the subject of mocking, has become a respectable director and his way of acting has ceased to be the blank of ironic comments.
Argo is her third feature film, after "Adieu petite, Adiós" (2007) and the thriller "The Town.
At the same time, it is Affleck's first film in which the action does not take place in the city of Boston, where he was raised.
Similarly, the sensitivity to capture the atmosphere of the place was a characteristic that placed old film directors above Hollywood standards.
And Affleck demonstrates it in Argo, where Tehran is “turning” in Canada.
The best scenes of the film take place in the streets, in the reconstruction of true events.The introductory sequence of embassy taking is impressive for its synoptic ability that, at the same time, transmits the emotion of dismay and lack of forecast that arises when, somewhere, the story takes a step forward.
Affleck and his collaborators get a similar effect on fictional scenes (the impostor team in Tehran’s bazar).
Too much action in too many places
